{
  "texts": [
    "In total, the dataset encompasses 16,878 training samples, 2,826 validation samples, and 5,488 test samples, with a distribution ratio of 7:1:2 respectively.",
    "This balanced distribution enables robust model training and evaluation, facilitating the development of effective intrusion detection systems capable of accurately discerning between benign network traffic and malicious intrusions.",
    "Evaluation metricsPrecision, Recall, and F1-score are the measures used in the named entity recognition.",
    "P (Positive) represents positive samples in all the samples.",
    "N (Negative) represents negative samples in all the samples."
  ]
}